author: COMSOL
description: This example demonstrates how to perform uncertainty quantification analysis of the Ishigami function. This random function of three variables is a well-known benchmark used to test global sensitivity analysis and uncertainty quantification algorithms. The mean, standard deviation, maximum, and minimum values as well as Sobol indices of the Ishigami function can be calculated analytically for the input distributions used here.
